I agree with the cook's from PA and VA about the method of cooking for this cut of meat. Therefore, I chose to make this in the oven but with thick-cut pork loin chops. They were tasty! The sauce was delicious and so easy to make. I bet they would also be great on the grill with the sauce used for the last 5-10 minutes of cooking.

Rating: 4
This is my new favorite "BBQ" sauce! The next day, I mixed the sauce with a little mayo, spread it on crackers and topped it with grilled slices of chicken sausage. Tonight I spread it on pizza dough [thin],topped it with slices of pepperoni, buffalo mozzarella and crumbled Gorgonzola cheese. Baked it at 450 degrees for 10 minutes. My point is that this sauce is very versatile and delicious! Thank you.

