One of my favorite bbq sauce recipes! Very easy to make. I made double the recipe and have it on hand for other dishes!

Rating: 3
After reading the other reviews, I decided to place the spareribs in a baking dish, sprinkle them with salt and pepper, cover them tightly with foil and bake in a 325 degree oven for about 2 hours. I prepared the glaze as directed, adding about 1/2 tsp. of chipolte chile powder. When the ribs were done in the oven, I drained the juice, spooned on some of the glaze, covered them back up and let them set for about 30 minutes. I then put them on a hot grill and basted them with the remaining sauce. They were excellent. I will try this glaze on baby backs, they are our favorites.

