Easy and tasty. One of our favorite recipes when we want to be fancy, but don't want to work at it.

Rating: 3
I've made this several times and really like it. While I agree that the cleanup can be quite messy, I generously coat the pan with cooking spray. One reader said that the ribs were rubbery, etc. and felt that this wasn't particularly good for ribs. I put a piece of foil over the ribs, place them on a broiler pan and this seems to solve the problem of both rubbery and greasy.

Rating: 3
This is a great tip I learned from some Chinese freinds. When cooking ribs in the oven, place them on a rack with some liquid under them. It can be water, juice, wine, etc. Ribs turn out exceptionally moist this way. Just make sure the liquid doesn't burn out before the cooking is finished. Put the glaze on the last 15 minutes. You won't be disappointed.

